        “Private, confidential, or proprietary information” means information which is owned or controlled by CDI and has not been publicly released or has not otherwise become common knowledge. This includes information of third parties in the possession of CDI that CDI is obligated to maintain in confidence. Examples of such information include:
        <ol class="indent-2">
            <li>
