            </li>
            <li>
                Scientific/engineering information, e.g., materials, processes, designs of apparatus and equipment, engineering aids, installation manuals, and computer software, and architecture. “Software” means any nontrivial, executable computer program routine, whether in source or object code;
            </li>
            <li>
                Technical management information, e.g., proposals;
            </li>
            <li>
                Financial information, e.g., service cost data, revenue, and profit margins;
            </li>
            <li>
                Business and marketing information relating to legal and regulatory matters, e.g., proposals, financial data, upcoming new ventures or acquisitions, customer information, including billing information;
            </li>
            <li>
                Personnel information, e.g., salaries, job assignments, and skills.
            </li>
        </ol>
